newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds trade picks up on Chicago reversal.
newsitem.headline: European feeds trade picks up on Chicago reversal.

text.p: Calls for a stronger Chicago soymeal futures opening sparked demand for nearby material in Europe, market sources said.

"Buying interest increased as Chicago opened firmer on fears for frost in the U.S. Midwest. And with Germany closed on Thursday many operators there covered nearby needs with the idea the market had reached a bottom," one broker said.
Afloat Argentine soymeal pellets traded between $275 and $277 a tonne cif Rotterdam from different vessels, Sept and Oct shipment also changed hands at $277 cif.
EU rapemeal traded at firmer levels as nearby material remains scarce because many crushers were not running at full capacity.
Oct rapemeal traded from 28.25 to 28.75 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine, Nov at 28.75, Nov/Jan at 28.75 and Feb/April at 28.85 marks fob lower Rhine.
Afloat Argentine sunmeal pellets traded at $147 a tonne cif Rotterdam, Sept at $148 and Oct at $149 a tonne cif.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
